{"id":89137,"title":"Endovascular treatment in an unusual case of direct carotid cavernous fistula.","abstract":"We describe a unique and unusual case of post-traumatic direct carotid cavernous fistula (CCF) with occluded proximal internal carotid artery and CCF filling from the contralateral side with retrograde cortical venous reflux. A male patient presented with intracranial haemorrhage due to cortical venous reflux. He was treated endovascularly through a contralateral approach by coiling the cavernous sinus and occluding the distal internal carotid artery at the fistulous site with glue. ","date":"2014-04-22","categories":"Wounds and Injuries","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24750711","annotations":[{"name":"Cerebral cortex","weight":0.809257,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cerebral_cortex"},{"name":"Cavernous sinus","weight":0.791621,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cavernous_sinus"},{"name":"Internal carotid artery","weight":0.773069,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internal_carotid_artery"},{"name":"Intracranial hemorrhage","weight":0.766442,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intracranial_hemorrhage"},{"name":"Vascular occlusion","weight":0.736569,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vascular_occlusion"},{"name":"Vein","weight":0.735569,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vein"},{"name":"Bleeding","weight":0.71741,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bleeding"},{"name":"Paranasal sinuses","weight":0.704684,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paranasal_sinuses"},{"name":"Artery","weight":0.684152,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artery"},{"name":"Fistula","weight":0.660011,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fistula"},{"name":"Common carotid artery","weight":0.323843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Common_carotid_artery"},{"name":"Cranial cavity","weight":0.275382,"